# Trivy ignore list for the lama-sidecar image scans (CI and release).
#
# The scan runs with ignore-unfixed, so unpatched base-OS CVEs (nothing we can
# action) don't wedge the build. This file is for a *fixable* HIGH/CRITICAL we
# consciously accept anyway: one CVE ID per line, with a comment on the line
# above stating why (why the vulnerable path can't be hit here, or why the fix
# is deferred). An entry without a rationale counts as unreviewed — remove it.
#
# Example:
# # only exploitable via feature X; not installed/enabled in this image
# CVE-2099-12345
